{
  "doc_id": "51448",
  "text": "In experimental tumour models, increased expression of VEGF has been associated with increased tumour growth. Transfection of VEGF into a breast carcinoma cell line increased in vivo tumour growth and vessel density [CITATION_1] . In a similar study, overexpression of VEGF by a melanoma cell line increased tumour growth, angiogenesis and experimental metastasis [CITATION_2] . In another study, the growth and vascularity of a rat glioma cell line in nude mice decreased after transfection with an antisense VEGF construct [CITATION_3] .",
